  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nIn the process of work on #9394 the #9475 PR has implemented automatic `mailserver` selection based on TCP ping using the `mailserver_ping` JSON RPC call, but it did not modify the UI to display to the user the newly available data.\r\n\r\nAn improved design was proposed by @errorists :\r\n\r\n![servers](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4932774/69126482-99d6dc00-0aa8-11ea-89d8-640f5963c7bb.png)\r\n\r\nSince this change is not in scope of V1 it's was not done as part of #9475.\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\nThe UI displays the info about mailservers to the user:\r\n\r\n* RTT(Round Trip Time) of the mailserver\r\n* Availability, possible with an error returned from the RPC call\r\n* Distinguishes between recommended(based on RTT and availability) and others\r\n\r\n### Notes\r\n\r\nYou can read about how the JSON RPC call works here:\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-go/blob/develop/rtt/README.md",
